        <section id="logic" class="grid-wrapper section">
            <p class="large-text">
                The objective is to replace legacy scroll event listeners with <b>Intersection Observer API</b> to achieve 60fps performance and eliminate layout thrashing during "sticky" state transitions.
            </p>

            <div class="card">
                <div>
                    <h3>Legacy Logic</h3>
                    <p>window.onscroll triggers layout recalculations on every frame.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-code">
                    window.addEventListener('scroll', ...);<br>
                    // High CPU overhead
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card accent">
                <div>
                    <h3>New System</h3>
                    <p>Observer patterns decoupling scroll position from DOM mutations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-code">
                    new IntersectionObserver(...)<br>
                    // Optimized performance
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div>
                    <h3>Swiss Grid</h3>
